      <title>[Letter] 1838 Jan. 2, Decatur, Alabama [to] James F. Smith, Newark, New Jersey / J.J.G. Smith</title>
   </titleInfo>
   <abstract>This document is a letter dated January 2, 1838, from J.J.G. Smith to his brother James Smith regarding a trip he plans to take up North. Smith also mentions that he hopes to see his brother and family while he is up North.</abstract>
